reloader /stakator 


Problem: ConfigMap updates don't automatically propagate to running Pods
Manual Solution: kubectl rollout restart deployment/name (tedious, error-prone)
Reloader Solution: Auto-detects config changes and triggers deployments

Workflow
ğŸ“ Update ConfigMap: kubectl apply -f config.yaml
ğŸ” Reloader detects change
ğŸ”„ Automatically triggers deployment rollout
ğŸš€ New pods start with updated config
â¹ï¸ Old pods terminate gracefully

scalable need not multiple restarts

install

helm repo add stakater https://stakater.github.io/stakater-charts
helm repo update
helm install reloader stakater/reloader -n reloader --create-namespace

verify installation

# Check pods are running
kubectl get pods -n reloader

# Check logs to confirm it's working
kubectl logs -l app=reloader-reloader -n reloader



apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: your-app
  annotations:
    reloader.stakater.com/auto: "true"

2. Specific ConfigMap
    configmap.reloader.stakater.com/reload: "app-config"

3. Specific Secret
    secret.reloader.stakater.com/reload: "app-secret"
